  "prompt": "How does it feel to marry your childhood crush?",
  "response": "Marrying your childhood crush can be a mix of excitement, nostalgia, and fulfillment. It often brings back sweet memories of young love and a sense of familiarity. There can be a deep emotional connection, having shared a significant part of your life together, which can make the bond feel even stronger. \n\nFor many, it's a dream come true, bringing joy and a sense of completeness. However, it can also come with the pressure of living up to the idealized version of that crush from childhood, which may lead to a need for open communication and understanding in the relationship. Overall, it's a unique and special experience that blends history with the promise of a shared future.",
